column5: For all you Red Lake fisherman, how thick is the ice about now? If you stop in at Lakeside, tell Ernie it was a balmy 50 degrees in Denver today.
Well, I just got back from drilling a few holes and the ice is THICK, maybe 36", (on Lake Winter) Winter, Wisconsin. I have 2 thermometers and the temp is 31 below (-31), it's cool. Scott

Dogs I just saw Ernie and a couple of other guys take off to go laker fishing, I was going to go but heading out for a show tomorrow. -20F right now lots of snow and the ice is about 30in. thick on Gullrock.
